# Parts

To build the filter I bought the [Nevermore StealthMax V2 kit][] from [onetwo3d.co.uk][] and I [bought printed parts from jb3d][].
I dislike buying printed parts but the filter is too big to print on a 250mm bed. Sad.

![Printed parts I had to buy.](/images/nevermore_stealthmax_v2/printed_parts.jpg)

The printed parts were good though, better than what I could've produced.

# Assembly

The documentation is a work in progress and you have to refer to the CAD to see how to assemble it.
The electronics however came with good documentation.

## Electronics

![The fan and electronics mounted into the flow chamber.](/images/nevermore_stealthmax_v2/electronics.jpg)

::: tip
It's easier to flash the Raspberry Pi before mounting and connecting it.
And make sure to use the correct version (`pico` or `pico w`).
:::

