## Broken pieces

I broke quite a few pieces during the assembly (but luckily not any of the big pieces I cannot reprint).

I was going to install the pixel holder as I got LEDs with the kit, but after breaking it several times I just installed the regular boring variant.

![The pixel holder broke in this way multiple times.](/images/nevermore_stealthmax_v2/nevermore_broken_pixel_holder.jpg)

![If felt like these clips broke every time I tried to insert or remove them.](/images/nevermore_stealthmax_v2/broken_things.jpg)

I don't know if it's a print calibration issue on my end but the printed parts I bought had the same issue.

# Vent servo software setup

There were no notes on how to configure the vent servo in the documentation but I managed to figure it out.

As a baseline I started with a min/max pulse width:

```
vent_servo_pulse_width_min: 0.001
vent_servo_pulse_width_max: 0.002
```

Then we can start moving the servo with this command:

```
NEVERMORE_VENT_SERVO_SET PERCENT=0.5 HOLD_FOR=0.1
```

We should find the edges for when the servo opens and closes.
For me the flap was open at 55% and closed at 70%.

Then we should reconfigure the min/max pulse ranges so that 0% means open and 100% means closed.
This is a linear system so we use this formula:

```
range_start + range_width * percentage
```

For me it looks like this:

```
# 0.001 + (0.002 - 0.001) * 0.55 = 0.00155
vent_servo_pulse_width_min: 0.00155
# 0.001 + (0.002 - 0.001) * 0.70 = 0.00170
vent_servo_pulse_width_max: 0.00170
```

So now I close the vent with:

```
NEVERMORE_VENT_SERVO_SET PERCENT=1 HOLD_FOR=0.1
```

and open it with:

```
NEVERMORE_VENT_SERVO_SET PERCENT=0 HOLD_FOR=0.1
```

